  "prompt": "Is there a way to sort by the most upvoted answers on Quora?",
  "response": "Yes, Quora provides a way to sort answers based on their upvote counts. Sorting answers by votes allows you to view the most upvoted (and often most informative or popular) responses at the top. Here's how you can do this:\n\n### Sorting Answers by Votes on Quora\n\n1. **Navigate to the Question:**\n   - Go to the Quora website or open the Quora app.\n   - Use the search bar to find the question you're interested in, or navigate to it through your feed.\n\n2. **Locate the Sorting Options:**\n   - Once you're on the question page, scroll down to view the answers.\n   - At the top of the answers section, you'll typically find a dropdown menu or sorting options labeled something like \"Sort,\" \"Sort By,\" or with icons representing sort functions.\n\n3. **Select \"By Votes\":**\n   - Click on the dropdown menu.\n   - From the available options, select **\"By Votes\"** or **\"Most Upvoted\"**. This option arranges the answers starting with the highest upvoted ones.\n\n4. **View the Sorted Answers:**\n   - After selecting the sorting option, the page will refresh (or the answers list will update) to display the answers in order of their upvote counts, with the most upvoted answers appearing first.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Default Sorting:** By default, Quora may sort answers based on a combination of factors, including upvotes, the credibility of the answerer, and engagement metrics. Using the \"By Votes\" option ensures that upvote count is the primary sorting criterion.\n\n- **Mobile vs. Desktop:** The interface may vary slightly between the Quora mobile app and the desktop website, but the sorting functionality is generally available on both platforms.\n\n- **Updates and Changes:** Quora periodically updates its interface and features. If you don't see the \"By Votes\" option, it might have been moved or renamed. Look for similar terminology or check Quora's help center for the latest guidance.\n\n- **Using Search Filters:** While Quora doesn't offer advanced search filters based on answer upvotes across the entire platform, sorting within individual questions as described above is the primary method to view highly upvoted answers.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily access the most upvoted answers to any question on Quora, helping you find the most valued and relevant responses quickly.",
